<subSubSection id="22E9F16736820871DAE1D881D6FE6EF7" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" type="notes">
<paragraph id="ABAA90607C39E7C32F8381ABB9B38085" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A4E7198F80CDF5A659A4440A82BED503" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176">
This species was commonly encountered in the sandy washes immediately surrounding MDRS (Fig. 31). Widely variable across its range, 
<bibRefCitation id="40BAD30E69C782022F48574091A8C47D" author="Welsh, S. L." journalOrPublisher="Print Services, Brigham Young University, Provo" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" title="A Utah Flora" year="1993">Welsh et al. (1993)</bibRefCitation>
report nine named varieties in Utah, and 
<bibRefCitation id="AE32E2A52C887354A74C48836ECA5AB5" author="Harris, JG" journalOrPublisher="Great Basin Naturalist" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" pagination="79 - 87" title="A vascular flora of the San Rafael Swell, Utah" volume="43" year="1983">Harris (1983)</bibRefCitation>
reports 
<taxonomicName id="762DB1377197B5570E03C3E3F9026F43" authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Chironomidae" genus="L." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="L. montanum var. jonesii" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="variety" species="montanum" variety="jonesii">L. montanum var. jonesii</taxonomicName>
(Rydb.) C.L. Hitch. from the nearby San Rafael Swell. 
<bibRefCitation id="C23B803FAFCF2FE9368F1E19721D582C" author="Al-Shebaz, IA" editor="Flora of North America Editorial Committee, eds." journalOrPublisher="New York and Oxford" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" title="Flora of North America North of Mexico" year="2010">Al-Shebaz and Gaskin (2010)</bibRefCitation>
subsume these varieties into 
<taxonomicName id="DB5E989206A4592058D27225E72C1106" authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Chironomidae" genus="L." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="L. montanum" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="species" species="montanum">L. montanum</taxonomicName>
sensu lato pending a thorough study of infraspecific delimitation; we follow their treatment here.
</paragraph>
